<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="Includes calibrations from the GIS-507 that are neither Global A or B specific.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>15</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>2/19/15</Date>
    <Description>Fixed some values and added driver workload. Also removed ValetLockCode and PressAndHoldTiming cals since there no longer needed.</Description>
    <Author>Samer Khatib</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>8/13/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Dave Malkan, updated the default value for the DataServicesEnable CAL from True to False, because as Dave mentioned for MY18 Data Services: default = False (results in setting being hidden but not functionally off), will be applicable for all Regions. Also  updated the default value for the LocationServicesEnable CAL from True to False because as Dave mentions for MY18, this CAL needs to be set False for all Regions except Europe. So we'll have the default value for this CAL set to False, and just do release a CAL override to change the value to True for Europe only, and updated the descriptions for both of these CALs.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>9/3/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within this CalDef file made the following updates: 1.) Removed the CAL called Name, confirmed with James Stefanovski and Cody Hansen this CAL has no intended function and could be removed. 2.) Per request from Sanghyun Ryu, updated CAL usage for the Audio_Feedback_Speed_settings_iText_To_Speech_Speech_Rates_Values CAL to not show Low Radio usage. 3.) Removed the CalID reference that was shown in the description field for the ValetMaskMenu CAL.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>11/6/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from James Stefanovski updated the default value for the Audio_Feedback_Speed_settings_iText_To_Speech_Speech_Rates_Values CAL from 75 to 100 percent.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Eero Laansoo, GIS-507 Spec. Owner, updated the defined minimum value of the AudioVolumeTeenDriver CAL from 24 to 10. Eero also confirmed the update reflecting this new minimum value update for this CAL will also be reflected in the next GIS-507 Spec. release as well. Also, Cody Hansen and Eero Laansoo confirmed the TeenDriverSpeedLockout and ValetModeSpeedLockout CALs were both incorrectly defined as Integer type CALs. Both CALs should have been defined as Enumeration type CALs instead since both of these CALs are driver work load CALs,, and need to be assoissicated to the DriverWorkload.enumdef the same as how the other driver work load CALs are handled. In order to do this, deleting the TeenDriverSpeedLockout CAL(CalID: _Bl6HAHsXEeSBuspje1a-pg) that was defined as an Integer type CAL, and this previously existing CAL needs to be replaced by the newly added TeenDriverSpeedLockout CAL (CalID: _jONJIN1hEeW58O1OdVks4w) that is defined as an Enumeration type CAL.  Also for this, deleted the ValetModeSpeedLockout (CalID: _Lx3ksHsXEeSBuspje1a-pg) that was defined as an Integer type CAL, and this previously existing CAL needs to be replaced by the newly added ValetModeSpeedLockout (CalID: _pgM8kN1qEeW58O1OdVks4w) that is defined as an Enumeration type CAL.  This update to define the TeenDriverSpeedLockout and ValetModeSpeedLockout as Enumeration type CALs instead of as Integer type CALs are also reflected in the latest published GIS-507 Spec., version 3.3.  Also, updated the Teen Driver Speed Limiter CAL defintion for what the ON setting represented from 82 MPH/132 km/h to 85 MPH/ 136 km/h to reflect this update made in the latest published GIS-507 Spec., version 3.3.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added a new calibration called TimeFormat that was added to the GIS-507 Spec. for configuring via a calibration the time format to be displayed in either a 12 hr or 24 hr format.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef added the following calibrations: AmbientLightingInfoPageVersion, AmbientLightingEnable, and AmbientLightingInformationViewDriverWorkload from the GIS-507</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>1/25/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS507_Settings.caldef file, added the following four new calibrations: 1.) TLAAlertAndBrakeInformationAvailable, 2.) AdjustablePedalspresent, 3.) AdjustableColumnpresent, and 4.) AdjustableMirrorsp.resent in the latest version of the GIS-507.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>2/13/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file, updated maximum speed limit shown in the description of the TeenDriverSpeedWarning calibration to show as 75 MPH instead of 70 MPH to align with what is shown in the function description of this calibration in the latest GIS-507. Also, corrected the typo shown for the equivalent km/h minumum and maximum speed values shown in the description of this calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>3/3/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS507_Settings.caldef to support RTC CR#: 1343166 added a new driver workload calibration called EnableNotificationReaderPopupDriverWorkload.  Also,  updated the default value of the TeenDriverSpeedLockout driver work load calibration from a value of NotParkedTeen = Trigger Level Value of 4  to Medium Speed = Trigger Level Value of 3 to reflect the default value this calibration has referenced in the latest version GIS-507. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>9/28/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS507_Settings.caldef,  removed usage of the LocationServicesEnable calibration for CSM. Per team discussions with the GM and CSM supplier teams on this, the rationale for this is that it is now required for the CSM to always display the Location service menu item to be CTS compliant. Therefore, the CSM supplier has already removed the functionality in software to use the LocationServicesEnable calibration to be able to calibrate ON or OFF the Location Service menu itemin software. The Location Service menu item is now always hardcode in the CSM software to always show. Since the LocationServicesEnable calibration no longer has a use case for the CSM, removing usage of this calibration for CSM only, and leaving usage of this calibration for Low Radio since this calibration still has a calibration use case for the Low Radio. Also, Within the GIS507_Settings.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef, except for two calibrations{ (1.) NotificationReaderPopupDriverWorkload, and 2.) Audio_Feedback_Speed_settings_iText_To_Speech_Speech_Rates_Values. Note, did not add GEM usage for these two calibrations since both of these calibraions did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>1/25/2018</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS507_Settings.caldef file, removed usage of CSM (MID and HIGH) for the TeenDriverEnableDisable calibration since it was confirmed this calibration is not being used by the CSM. Instead of using this calibration to determine whether or not to display the Teen Driver menu item, the CSM uses the status of the Teen Driver available message from the BCM to determine whether or not to display the Teen Driver menu item.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>05/02/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR# 1737940, added one new enumeration calibration called TRANSMITTER_POCKET_LOCATION along with the associated enumeration values within the GIS-507_Settings.enumdef file. Also, per CR# 1291582, Removed Touchscreen_Calibration and CalibrateTouchscreenDriverWorkload from the GIS507_Settings.caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>Emmanuel Oleka</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="This CAL is used to show the corresponding image on the radio display of the pocket location for a given vehicle the user will be instructed to put their keyless transmitter in for teen driver key transmitter learning. For more information on this CAL see Sec&#xac;tion 3.5.2.5.1 in the GIS-507. " Name="TRANSMITTER_POCKET_LOCATION" References="GIS-507 Section 3.5.2.6 MY21 REGISTERING KEYLESS TRANSMITTERS" Usage="MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_XtdusFIjEeibCblrVhJh5A</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>05/02/2018</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release of this Calibration</Description>
      <Author>Emmanuel Oleka</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_iDSUAFIYEeibCblrVhJh5A</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
