  <CalDefinition Description="Location Services: When the calibration is set to False, the setting is hidden and location services is on by default. When the calibration is set to True, the setting is shown and location services is on by default. Calibration default = False" Name="LocationServicesEnable" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_fhAzwLhrEeSmdeXBYRoUqg</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>8/13/2015</Date>
      <Description>Per request from Dave Malkan, updated the default value for the LocationServicesEnable CAL from True to False, and updated the description this CAL.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>9/28/2017</Date>
      <Description>Removed usage of the LocationServicesEnable calibration for CSM. Per team discussions with the GM and CSM supplier teams on this, the rationale for this is that it is now required for the CSM to always display the Location service menu item to be CTS compliant. Therefore, the CSM supplier has already removed the functionality in software to use the LocationServicesEnable calibration to be able to calibrate ON or OFF the Location Service menu itemin software. The Location Service menu item is now always hardcode in the CSM software to always show. Since the LocationServicesEnable calibration no longer has a use case for the CSM, removing usage of this calibration for CSM only, and leaving usage of this calibration for Low Radio since this calibration still has a calibration use case for the Low Radio. Also, updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Data Services: When the calibration is set to False, the setting is hidden and data services is on by default. When the calibration is set to True, the setting is shown and data services is on by default. Calibration default = False" Name="DataServicesEnable" References="Gis507 5.1.1.1*MY17 Calibration Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_lTOC8LhrEeSmdeXBYRoUqg</CalID>
